                <h1>The Yellow Wallpaper: Analyzing Literary Devices</h1>
                <p>The Yellow Wallpaper utilizes various literary devices to enhance its themes of mental illness and oppression. The use of symbolism is prominent, with the wallpaper itself representing the constraints placed on women. Additionally, the first-person narrative allows for an intimate exploration of the protagonistâ€™s psyche, while irony underscores the contrast between societal expectations and personal freedom.</p>
